bilingual.source: She has got a brother and a sister.
bilingual.target: 她有一个兄弟和一个姐妹。

bilingual.source: This is your brother or sister's daughter.
bilingual.target: 这是你兄弟或姐妹的女儿。

bilingual.source: I heard the trip was to visit our sister school in Boston.
bilingual.target: 我听说这次旅行是去拜访我们在波士顿的姐妹学校。

bilingual.source: I share a room with my sister.
bilingual.target: 我和我的姐妹共用一个房间。

bilingual.source: I often go shopping with my sister.
bilingual.target: 我经常和我的姐妹一起去购物。

bilingual.source: My sister is very good at playing the piano.
bilingual.target: 我的姐妹非常擅长弹钢琴。

list.abstract: SISTAR（씨스타），是STARSHIP entertainment于2010年6月4日推出的韩国四人女子组合，由尹宝拉（宝拉/BoRa）、孝琳（HyoLyn）、昭宥（SoYou）、金多顺（多顺/DaSom）组成。 2010年6月3日，SISTAR推出首张单曲专辑《Push Push》，第二天在KBS“音乐银行”中首次亮相，并正式出道；同年10月，获得第17届大韩民国演艺艺术赏女子组合歌手赏。2011年4月，由尹宝拉、孝琳组成子团体SISTAR19；同年8月9日，SISTAR正式发行正规一辑《So Cool》。2012年4月12日，发行第一张迷你专辑《ALONE》。2016年6月21日，发行第四张迷你专辑《没我爱》，主打曲为《I Like That》。2017年5月23日，在粉丝官咖上留言发表了解散的决定；同年6月，发行告别单曲专辑《LONELY》，正式解散。
sister，英语单词，名词、形容词，意为“姐妹；（称志同道合者）姐妹；修女；护士；姐妹般的；同类型的”。

yingyinNormal.en: What is the worse part? I can't remember which sister.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那最糟糕的是什么？我不记得是哪个姐妹。

yingyinNormal.en: Why, what happened? I fooled around with Joey's sister. Well, that's not the worst part.
yingyinNormal.zh: 怎么了？出了什么事？我跟乔伊的姐妹瞎搞，这还不是最糟糕的。

yingyinNormal.en: While Yan and her sister pick up some last-minute decorations from the market, the men of the family including 3-year-old Zhi Yuan have an important appointment.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当张家姐妹拾缀一些市面卖的年尾饰品时，家里包括3岁的致远在内的男性，有个重要的约会。

yingyinNormal.en: You know, sister things, like I never liked how she always borrowed my bras, or she never liked how I stole her one chance to escape the village and I left her there, taking care of my mother. Things like that.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你懂的，姐妹间的小摩擦，比如我很讨厌她总是借我的胸罩，而她也很讨厌我抢了她离开小村庄的机会而把她留在那里，照顾我母亲，类似的事情。

yingyinNormal.en: I see her in my sister Prim.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在我心中，她就像我的妹妹。

yingyinNormal.en: My sister gets to keep her cat.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的妹妹可以留下她的猫。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm very disappointed in your sister.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我对你姐失望透了。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, come on, man. Bros before my sister.
yingyinNormal.zh: 拜托，伙计，男人如手足，女人如衣服，我妹亦然。

yingyinNormal.en: Yes? Hi, is Rachel here? I'm her sister.
yingyinNormal.zh: 哪一位？瑞秋在吗？我是她的妹妹。

yingyinNormal.en: Who can't go out with Leonard? My sister.
yingyinNormal.zh: 谁不能和莱纳德在一起？我妹妹。

yingyinNormal.en: She's my sister. She would never hurt me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她是我的姐姐，她永远不会伤害我。

yingyinNormal.en: You didn't tell me you had a sister, Jenny.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你可没告诉我你有这么个姐姐啊，珍妮。

yingyinNormal.en: My sister loved him. She bore his children.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我姐姐爱他，怀了他的孩子。

yingyinNormal.en: How? Everyone's either a dude or our sister.
yingyinNormal.zh: 行不通，都是男的和一个姐姐。

yingyinNormal.en: What are you talking about? You're my sister.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你在说什么？你可是我姐姐。

yingyinNormal.en: Men will one day sing songs about me, sister.
yingyinNormal.zh: 终有一日人们会颂扬我的，姐姐。

yingyinNormal.en: Yes. My sister's uterus came down with a baby.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对的，我姐的子宫要"生"小孩了。

yingyinNormal.en: Your foundation literally saved my sister's...
yingyinNormal.zh: 您设的基金救了我妹妹的...

yingyinNormal.en: Boy, did we make friends with the wrong sister?
yingyinNormal.zh: 孩子们，我们是不是不该跟姐姐交朋友。

yingyinNormal.en: Who is this man? I don't know. Her sister's son.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这人是什么人？不知道，她姐姐的儿子。

examination_example.sentence: A quantitative-based one, for example, is unlikely to be sent home, where one could ask their older brothers and <highlight>sisters</highlight> to help.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 例如，基于数量的方法不太可能被送回家，在那里人们可以请他们的哥哥姐姐帮忙。

examination_example.sentence: So, for example, my <highlight>sister</highlight>'s birthday is December 9th and her golden birthday would have been the year she turns 9 years old.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 例如，我姐姐的生日是12月9日，她的黄金生日应该是她9岁的那一年。

examination_example.sentence: What did the woman's parents do on her <highlight>sister</highlight>'s lucky birthday?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这位女士的父母在她姐姐的幸运生日做了什么？

examination_example.sentence: A few years ago, my <highlight>sister</highlight> in-law started to feel worried about her teenage daughter.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 几年前，我的嫂子开始担心她十几岁的女儿。

examination_example.sentence: "He doesn't pay you enough to live on," his <highlight>sister</highlight> told him.
examination_example.sentence_trans: "他付给你的钱不足以让你活下去，"他的妹妹告诉他。

examination_example.sentence: "I don't like cabbage, " cried Sophia, Henry's little <highlight>sister</highlight>, at the table．
examination_example.sentence_trans: "我不喜欢卷心菜，"亨利的妹妹索菲亚在餐桌上喊道。
